snapshot.subject: Offline request handling
snapshot.description:
As a user I want the requests made to be Asynchronous so that I don't lose the response data.

Definition of Done:
* Be able to grab response even when the web page is not focused

Acceptance Criteria:
* User Local Browser Storage to store response
* Render the data when back the web page is focused
* Use useEffect Hooks to render the data
* Constantly check if the response data is received

![](https://media-protected.taiga.io/attachments/7/0/9/0/e11ef03f2adc3e5e067cc0f4d4aab7e3fbea74b2ffe7221f614b14fae149/image.png?token=YkprWQ%3AYQv4XvKJKb-NMT8xRGiTHyzYL1LSCmzCNDaMX3jVSJBo4klX1Shm9pZLxAEZbVnKzPA5LYKM4RirSoGJeca-gg#_taiga-refresh=wikipage:1580068)

**What went well:**

*   Setting up codebase using React-Typescript.
*   Visualization using sample data from other projects instead of waiting for the actual data to stream, thus avoiding delays.
*   Team interaction and collaboration.
*   Since we were able to close 78% of the stories and couldn't close only 1 task in one User Story. We can say that we could achieve most of our sprint goal.
*   Good Git branching strategy. 

**What could have been better:**

*   We started off with a slow pace though were able to pick it up during the mid to end phase.
*   We couldn't close task #7 in User Story #5 due to incompatible sample data.  

**What we will change for the next sprint:**

*   Deliver value at a constant pace from start.
*   Try to achieve 100% of the goal.

**Minutes of Standups:** [**https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AqLDBa\_2qXeW\_6kBAxT--FpCQhHYDnIkyMOENPLTmes/edit?usp=sharing**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AqLDBa_2qXeW_6kBAxT--FpCQhHYDnIkyMOENPLTmes/edit?usp=sharing)

Sprint 2

GitHub Repo: https://github.com/SER-516-Project-BullPen-Group-B/Team5_front_end

Individual Contribution: https://docs.google.com/document/d/19FaMnqPkmR4OOD1XgLA5ujqg6ogLqlcYKs78nDxkkfo/edit

Scrum Master: Achuth Reddy Rajula

Team Members:

  • Varshik Sonti
  • Kousthubha Kalvakolanu
  • RajaLaxman Rao Thakkalapelli
  • Achuth Reddy Rajula

Minutes of Standups: https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AqLDBa_2qXeW_6kBAxT--FpCQhHYDnIkyMOENPLTmes/edit?usp=sharing

Sprint 2 Planning :               
Sprint Goal: Interact with API Gateway to fetch the project data and visualize the metrics, also work on improving the existing interface.  

The following points  were discussed and are converted into their respective user stories before proceeding with sprint 2:

  • Maintain persistent response data by implementing support to offline requests and browser storage (5 points)
  • Add a Nav Bar to create a simple yet effective user flow for the user (3 points)
  • Visualize Cycle Time, Lead, Lead Time, CFD, WIP, Active Tasks, Niko Niko by fetching data from their respective microservices teams via API Gateway (4 points for each microservice)

Story points were estimates using scrum poker

Attendees of the planning: Achuth Rajula, Varshik Sonti, Kousthubha Kalvakolanu, RajaLaxman Rao Thakkalapelli

Sprint 2 Review:  https://asu.zoom.us/rec/share/5rsZBE4JNr8G1yMOsBsDDriE5KrGcFaV8JCAhQ_-pNfwC32QvwlbZFHGgkh4SKl1._cw7jS1ae0OTcMER Passcode: 3XGib&w+

Yes, met the sprint goal. we can call this sprint a success because we were able to meet the sprint goal and deliver 5 metrics.

Burndown: Our burndown is as close as possible to the ideal rate

Final sprint board:

Sprint 2 Retrospective:

Things that went well:

  • Our burndown is as close as possible to the ideal burndown!
  • Good git branching strategy
  • We were able to close 88% of the user stories and couldn't close only 1 task in one user story due to a blocker from the microservice team.
  • Team collaboration, and collective code ownership
  • Added Defensive Programming paradigm to ensure the built system doesn't break when unexpected inputs are given
  • Added Code Reusability paradigm to reuse a component to eliminate redundancy and complexity in the codebase
  • Achieved a 100% score on codiga's code quality

Things that did not go well:

  • Increased delay towards expected deliverables from other teams

Things to do in future sprints:

  • Interact more frequently with other teams outside formal calls and meetups to positively influence the delivery time of the expected deliverables
  • Be more rigid with the delivery of expected deliverables from other teams
  • Keep up the same good work in the future sprints

Decisions are taken in the last retrospective that went well:

  • Managed to deliver value from the start and at a constant rate
  • Close all tasks except for the blocker

Code Quality Policy:

  • We managed to keep our codebase clean with a 100% quality score and code grade A on codiga
  • We additionally conducted a google's lighthouse analysis which is an automated tool to check the quality of a web app

### Sprint 1

**Sprint 1 Planning :   **
Sprint Goal: Build an Interface to take user input and map API endpoints with the respective microservices.

:** [https://asu.zoom.us/rec/share/bh84PnAeCdTbj\_6dwKc9Y9\_uFDZZ3Fdcm2Oye\_5DbdTqKX91hi15rylOnxBJCdap.AY4y9RT-3fhXPmWf?startTime=1649043203000 (Passcode: b5v&#kUU](https://asu.zoom.us/rec/share/bh84PnAeCdTbj_6dwKc9Y9_uFDZZ3Fdcm2Oye_5DbdTqKX91hi15rylOnxBJCdap.AY4y9RT-3fhXPmWf?startTime=1649043203000))

**Sprint Retrospective :**

![](https://media-protected.taiga.io/attachments/7/0/9/0/e11ef03f2adc3e5e067cc0f4d4aab7e3fbea74b2ffe7221f614b14fae149/image.png?token=YkprWQ%3AYQv4XvKJKb-NMT8xRGiTHyzYL1LSCmzCNDaMX3jVSJBo4klX1Shm9pZLxAEZbVnKzPA5LYKM4RirSoGJeca-gg#_taiga-refresh=wikipage:1580068)

**What went well:**

* Setting up codebase using React-Typescript.
* Visualization using sample data from other projects instead of waiting for the actual data to stream, thus avoiding delays.
* Team interaction and collaboration.
* Since we were able to close 78% of the stories and couldn't close only 1 task in one User Story. We can say that we could achieve most of our sprint goal.
* Good Git branching strategy. 

**What could have been better:**

* We started off with a slow pace though were able to pick it up during the mid to end phase.
* We couldn't close task #7 in User Story #5 due to incompatible sample data.  

**What we will change for the next sprint:**

* Deliver value at a constant pace from start.
* Try to achieve 100% of the goal.

**Minutes of Standups:** [**https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AqLDBa\_2qXeW\_6kBAxT--FpCQhHYDnIkyMOENPLTmes/edit?usp=sharing**](https://docs.google.com/document/d/1AqLDBa_2qXeW_6kBAxT--FpCQhHYDnIkyMOENPLTmes/edit?usp=sharing)
